Necromancy the Greeks call it, but necromancy or hydromancy, whatever
you like to call it, is where the dead seem to speak. ... They were
devils that delighted in those obscene ministries, and under the names
of those whom the people held divine, got place to play their
impostures, and by illusive miracles to captivate all their souls.
